alidation phases), which had never been done in the\nliterature. In addition, since a part of the test dataset is similar to the\ntraining dataset, the proposed model obtains an accuracy of 98.82%. The\nrobustness is proved by adding another test dataset containing noisy and more\nor less ambiguous images to be classified. The model still manages to detect\nthese cases from its training of unambiguous cases, showing that the obtained\ngeneralization is efficient with an accuracy of 73.71%.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 17 Mar 2023 07:59:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-22"}
